<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-09-15T08:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-09-15T08:24:00-05:00" n="312" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60 p 31/23: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-09-15T15:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">September 15,
                                        1925—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September 15—10:47
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>81. Your 41, August 11, 3 p.m. Until general elections take place October
                            4th and new Government comes in, it is impossible to make any progress
                            in negotiations. Full particulars go forward in pouch this week.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Coleman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>